LAFIA – As the National Convention of the ruling, All Progressive Congress (APC), has gathered momentum Nasarawa Governor Abdullahi Sule and other APC stakeholders in the state have on Tuesday endorsed the aspiration of the immediate past governor of the state Tanko Al-Makura to become the next chairman of the ruling party. Governor Abdullahi Sule, who spoke during the endorsement ceremony said for now-former governor of Nasarawa State was the only candidate who has indicated to contest the position of national chairman of the party. He also gave assurances that if Senator Almakura eventually becomes the national Chairman he will uphold the APC constitution, respect the party’s organs, among others. 2023 Presidency: Over 600 Women Groups Back Yahaya Bello Aregbesola, Others To Interface On Alma Mata’s Renovation… Senator Al-makura currently the senator representing Nasarawa south senatorial. Sule said that Senator Almakura currently stands tall among all other aspirants in the race based on his experience, capability, integrity, and support among all interests in the party and above all being the only person Nasarawa knows. John Mamman, State APC Chairman, who also spoke at the occasion said if Al-Makura is elected will work towards ensuring that APC becomes a model in political party administration in Nigeria and beyond. Speaking on behalf of national assembly members, Godiya Akwashiki, the senator representing Nasarawa north extolled the political and administrative records of Senator Almakura assuring that he is the only candidate to take the party to the next level.